{"type":"message","id":"e2b2cacf","parentId":"91e1bbaa","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:32:54.522Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d7kg6zeyrxt1_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 052915\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/tic_experiment.py (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- Pending items include:\r\n  - Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n  - Define significance scoring for pulse content\r\n  - Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n  - Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n  - Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action mentioned is the **TIC Experiment**:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThis seems like the most actionable and specific next step. I should implement the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nFirst, let me check what pulse log files exist and their structure to understand what I'm working with.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next logical step, but I need to first examine the existing pulse log files to understand their structure before implementing the classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nExamine the pulse log directory structure and recent pulse file format to inform TIC implementation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n\r\n## Overview\r\nTest hypothesis: **Causal structure IS invariant structure** - compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Methodology\r\n1. Parse last 20 pulse logs from `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n2. Extract feature vectors from each pulse (file modifications, goal references, concepts)\r\n3. Classify each feature as **invariant** (stable across pulses) or **variant** (changing)\r\n4. Use invariant set to predict next pulse content\r\n5. Measure accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n## Implementation Plan\r\n- [ ] Parse pulse logs and extract feature corpus\r\n- [ ] Implement invariant/variant classifier\r\n- [ ] Build next-pulse predictor from invariants\r\n- [ ] Run on last 20 pulses\r\n- [ ] Validate against criteria\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n- Breakaway's stateless nature means each pulse is independent\r\n- Invariants = persistent structure across discontinuity\r\n- Variants = pulse-specific content\r\n\"\r\nfile: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 05:29:30\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774344774520}}
